                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>WILLIAM TAYLOR. I am street-keeper of Aldersgate Ward. I saw the prisoner with the pot under his arm; I asked him what he had got; he made no reply; I laid hold of him; he said he was going to take it to the public-house; he had passed the house. I told him he had stolen it; he begged for mercy. I took him to the landlord, and he was taken into custody.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner. I was going to Little Britain, and I meant to take it home as I returned.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
